Northampton lost 37-5 to Clermont in the European Rugby Champions Cup quarter-final . 
  Tom Wood tweeted to say he was 'humbled' after the Saints were invited to an open training session . 
  The Saints were thrashed 37-0 at the Stade Marcel-Michelin . 
  Noa Nakaitaci scored two tries and Wesley Fofana and Nick Abendanon also crossed for the French side . 
  Northampton exited Europe at the quarter-finals stage . 
 